  dialogueLines:
  - What splendor in your stride! Yet it seems a shield against unseen wounds. Peacock,
    why such fierce display in this lonely corner of the garden?
  - "Your intrusion is unwanted. My plumage is unmatched, yet they cast me out for
    Snake\u2019s lies. I am in no mood for your platitudes. Pester someone else! "
  - 'You boast unmatched beauty, yet banishment festers. Does this flamboyance truly
    heal the wound, or merely mask it? Isolation only deepens the shadow. '
  - "What could a mere wanderer like you know of such matters? You are only a child
    in these affairs. If you live to grow old, may fate rip your life\u2019s purpose
    away as it has mine\u2014then you might begin to understand. Until then, learn
    to keep your nose out of the business of your elders! "
  - "This \u201Ccelestial wealth\u201D you claim\u2014does it not echo the Painter\u2019s
    gift, yet hide a deeper truth? I have wandered deserts cast out as \u201Cmad,\u201D
    yet love revealed worth beyond appearances. Show me your true feathers; deception
    only betrays the soul. "
  - "You dare expose what I conceal? This\u2026 this lie was my armor! "
  - "Your new purpose lies not in borrowed glory, but confronting the deception and
    growing at your own pace. The snake\u2019s lies thrive in hiding; truth unfolds
    in time. "
  - "Insufferable\u2026"
  otherLines:
  - "Your intrusion is unwanted. My plumage is unmatched, yet they cast me out for
    Snake\u2019s lies. I am in no mood for your platitudes. Pester someone else! "
  - "You\u2026 speak as one who has tasted exile. But my paradise of perfection is
    lost forever to the snake. What use is your pity? "
  - "You followed\u2026 even with that cursed thing. Why? "
  - "Your words pierce deeper than any thorn. Isolation has only worsened this self-hatred.
    Leaning on another\u2026 it is not weakness?"
  - "Then I will return with you. This feather proves the snake\u2019s deception\u2014his
    lies that turned my pride to poison. I lashed out because I feared my own incompleteness.
    No more hiding. "
  - "You have shown me what the manuscripts whisper: outer splendor is illusion.
    The soul\u2019s pace is its own paradise. Thank you, wanderer. I am no longer
    banished from myself. "
